## Plan

**Scope (TIGHT, 1 bead = 1 commit):** Core slice ONLY — the `retro.Generator` runner seam + `etude retro generate <scope>` command that invokes a configured EXTERNAL generator script over the covered runs' resolved artifacts, then captures the produced retro through the SHIPPED Phase B `retro.Writer` path. `generate = Generator + the Phase B capture path`, exactly as `bench = Runner + Recorder + Judge + eval.Writer`. Generator is selected via an explicit `--generator <script>` flag (like replay `--runner`/bench `--judge`), with a `git config etude.retroGenerator` fallback. NO config block, NO automated triggers, NO sidecar, NO etude log — those are DEFERRED (see below).

**Approach:** Mirror the proven `replay.Runner` / `eval.Judge` seam shape verbatim. Add a one-method `retro.Generator` interface (`Generate(ctx, GenerateRequest) -> (GenerateResult, error)`) in internal/retro, with two implementations: `ExecGenerator` (external script, same strict-env exec contract as replay.ExecRunner / eval.ExecJudge) and `StubGenerator` (test double, mirrors StubRunner/StubJudge). The `retro generate` command resolves each `--subject-run` via replay.ResolveInputs (reusing the covered run's stage output + inputs, pinned to the resolved commit so it never re-resolves the ref — same as bench), materializes those bytes, builds a GenerateRequest, runs the generator to get the markdown body, then threads that body into the EXISTING retro capture path (artifactstore.AddContent role=retro + assemble workflow:retro manifest + retro.Writer.Write) — refactor the body-to-manifest assembly out of retroCaptureRunner.run into a shared helper so generate reuses it and the writer is NOT reinvented.

